# Design system for agents

Before creating or changing visual UI, read these files in order:

1. **`design.md`** (repo root) — authoritative spec: layout invariants, theme bounds, spacing tokens, hover/focus/motion rules, anti-patterns
2. **`.agents/skills/product-design/SKILL.md`** — workflow, checklist, surface references
3. **`src/design-guide.md`** — primitive classes (`.btn`, `.card`, `.text-heading`), CSS variables, theme data attributes
4. **`.cursor/rules/site-nav-css.mdc`** — nav is framework-controlled; never override from theme or new CSS

## Hard rules

- Use **`var(--color-*)`**, **`var(--spacing-*)`**, **`var(--duration-*)`**, **`var(--ease-*)`** — no arbitrary hex or hardcoded `0.3s` / `cubic-bezier(...)` in new code
- Cards are **never transparent** — no glassmorphism, no `opacity < 1` on card surfaces
- **No dimensional `:hover`** — do not change `padding`, `margin`, `gap`, `width`, or `height` on hover (color, shadow, transform only)
- **Nav is fixed** — themes cannot change nav height, padding, or pill layout; use `.site-nav` / `.nav-container`, never `.container` on nav markup
- **Hero layout is framework-owned** — full viewport width, flush to top, nav `position: fixed`; see `references/rules.md` § Layout invariants
- Prefer **Astro** for static UI; **React** only when client interactivity is required
- Reuse existing primitives from `src/styles/global.css` and modules under `src/styles/modules/` before inventing new patterns

## After UI changes

Run `npm run audit:design:check` (enforced in CI). Cloud agents: `npm run audit:ui:changed -- --check` before push. Report-only: `npm run audit:design` / `npm run audit:design:strict`. Repeated mistakes → log in `references/coverage-gaps.md` and extend `scripts/design-audit/`.
